Hi, I don't know adout Polish history lot, but I don't think that king Wladyslaw II (Jagiello) was so good. He was Bohemian king for while and was also known as King Bene (King Agree), as quite weak ruler, who let nobility to rule on their own.

Also king Wladyslaw I (Lokietek ~ The Short) doesn't seem to be so legendary leader as he was often defeated by Bohemian king Vaclav II (Waclaw II in your list

Yes Jagiello was a Bohemian king for a while, but this fact is even rarely mentioned in Polish history, he was almost 80 years old at that time, his major achievements were in Poland and Lithuania, not in Bohemia, which was even seen as dangerous ( Hussites) by Archbishop Oleshnicki - the real ruler in the last years of Jagiello's reign.

Lokietek maybe wasn't very successfull at the beginning, but in the end he became the king of Poland and united the country. He was often defeated by Vaclav II, but it was Lokietek who was victorious in the end.

It's BKB's choice what to do with those proposals.
